                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18350615-1585-offence-1 t18350615-name-1261"></join>William Read</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350615-name-1262" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1262" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1262" type="surname" value="READ"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1262" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM READ</persName>
                  </hi>. I was coachman to Captain Thomas, of Shepherd's Bush. I knew the prisoner there—he was with me on the 13th, 14th, and 15th of November—I lent him a shirt and coat—I took him to my bed-room, and laid out a clean shirt to lend him—I came down to dry a coat to put on my back, and was absent seven or eight minutes—I had opened my table-drawer that morning, to take out some money to pay for the prisoner's breakfast—I then left three sovereigns, and 13<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. in it—that was at half-past eight—he went about nine, that morning—I returned to the room, and he was gone, with the shirt—I then looked into the table<lb></lb>drawer, missed the three sovereigns and 13<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—nobody else had been in the room that morning—I lost sight of him a for long while, and met him again in Piccadilly, on the 16th of last May, and gave him in charge.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. This was eight years ago. <hi rend="italic">Witness</hi>. It was in 1827—his name is Ralph William Perry, not Read—I looked about for him, but never saw him till last May.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350615-name-1263" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1263" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1263" type="surname" value="LOCK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1263" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN LOCK</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable D</hi> 74.) The prisoner was given to me by the last witness, for robbing him of 3<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 13<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—he said he knew nothing</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183506150192"></xptr>
               <p>whatever of the money; and on taking him to the station-house, he said he went away with the shirt on his back.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner put in a written defence, declaring his innocence, and stating that there were other persons about the premises who could have commit<lb></lb>ted the robbery.)</p>
